Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the @penne pasta{180%g}.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{240%g} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Halfway through frying the chicken, add the @British smoked bacon lardons{90%g} to the pan and cook for the remaining time.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook it thoroughly.

Once the meat is cooked, stir in the garlic and @mixed herbs{1%sachet}. Cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Meanwhile, when your pan of water is boiling, add the penne and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

== Sauce ==

Add the @tomato passata{1%carton}, @red wine stock paste{28%g}, @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @water{75%ml} to the chicken.

Bring to a boil, then turn the heat down and simmer until slightly thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

While the sauce simmers, finely chop the @chives{1/2%bunch} (use #scissors{} if easier).

Once thickened, stir in the @peas{120%g} until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

== Finish ==

Once the sauce has thickened, stir through the @creme fraiche{75%g}, half the chives and Cheddar.

Add the cooked pasta and season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then stir to combine.

When ready, share the chicken and bacon pasta between your bowls.

Sprinkle over the remaining chives to finish.

Enjoy!